      <Docs>
        <summary>
            Each tab header takes up as much space as it needs.  This is similar to how WPF and Visual Studio Code behave.
            Suggest to keep <see cref="P:Microsoft.Toolkit.Uwp.UI.Controls.TabView.IsCloseButtonOverlay" /> set to false.
            <see cref="P:Microsoft.Toolkit.Uwp.UI.Controls.TabView.SelectedTabWidth" /> is ignored.
            In this scenario, tab width behavior is effectively turned off.  This can be useful when using custom styling or a custom panel for layout of <see cref="T:Microsoft.Toolkit.Uwp.UI.Controls.TabViewItem" /> as well.
            </summary>
