        <summary>
            Each tab header will fill to fit the available space.  If <see cref="P:Microsoft.Toolkit.Uwp.UI.Controls.TabView.SelectedTabWidth" /> is set, that will be used as a Maximum Width.
            This is similar to how Microsoft Edge behaves when used with the <see cref="P:Microsoft.Toolkit.Uwp.UI.Controls.TabView.SelectedTabWidth" />.
            Suggest to set <see cref="P:Microsoft.Toolkit.Uwp.UI.Controls.TabView.IsCloseButtonOverlay" /> to true.
            Suggest to set <see cref="P:Microsoft.Toolkit.Uwp.UI.Controls.TabView.SelectedTabWidth" /> to 200 and the TabViewItemHeaderMinWidth Resource to 90.
